You mentioned this interim role at lunch. Intrigued me. 

I‚Äôm talking to three separate investment firms tomorrow at same time. They participated in SureBright‚Äôs raise and have a overlapping portfolios across 23 companies from seed to Series C 

They want to intro me into the distressed portion of their shared portfolio. Think I mentioned this to you?

It‚Äôs a niche specialty I really am intrigued to explore during this time, among other options I have. It‚Äôs a fun time to explore options.

Their companies are all B2B and B2C SaaS but I‚Äôd be interested in learning more about any opportunity to work together in that capacity. I think half the battle in that role is building trust out the gate. Guys like SolTech are particular about who they let in.

We are setting up a formal consulting firm trying to really broker a lot of the m&a for series A-C size companies. I think definitely points of collaboration to be had. Whether needing interim consultants and trying to outsource biz dev, or just deal flow. We are in the early stages of the planning but sounds like more to explore here

Yea keep me in mind and I‚Äôll keep you in the loop on my end.

I‚Äôm exploring but also excited to have time back. I have an AI platform company I‚Äôve spent two years on with a research doctorate and a phd data scientist as equity partners that I‚Äôm raising a round for currently. 

It sits on top of years of published scientific research data and uses ChatGPT conversational AI to understand the user requests, reads thousands of papers, understands it, and conversationally drives the findings into workflows for institutional users who currently manually do all this. 

Haha it‚Äôs a mouthful
That sounds awesome

Spoke to Paul. It sounds like they were disappointed with their 2022 numbers and want to make a strong push in 2023 to justify their valuation. Paul suggested waiting until Q3 to formally revisit a public offering

I agree with his logic for the most part. I did say we should time an IPO with good news. So if they think they will do a great Q4, let‚Äôs hustle to get it done in time to be able to announce that after being public to create shareholder engagement off the bat.

There‚Äôs also a few things they can do to prepare for an audit and S-1 registration ahead of this, and so I am sending him a full roadmap so they can plan over the next few months and maybe cut the timeline from 120 days to 60 days
Amazing. Thank you and sounds good

I said there‚Äôs a chance we have a great deal fall on our laps sooner and will call to revisit. We have one shell company now with an active shareholder base and cash in the vehicle. It could be a great opportunity for an above market valuation. Something like that he said he‚Äôd be happy to visit sooner
Also gives us time to source other e-commerce deals to potentially uplist at the same time in Q3/4 which will make the biggest splash
